uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.forms.registry

Class HeirarchyFormRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.AbstractContexed
      • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.registry.FormFactoryProviderRegistry
        • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.forms.registry.HeirarchyFormRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    UIGenerator, Contexed, TransitionFactoryCreator, NodeMaker

    public class HeirarchyFormRegistry
extends FormFactoryProviderRegistry
    A FormProviderRegistry that automatically includes all tables whose implementation class is a sub-class of the class defined by class.root.tag.

    The name used for the form defaults to the construction tag of the factory but can be changed by setting registry-tag.factory-tag.name

    Update/create privilege is given to users via the (Update|Create)(tag|table-name) role.

    Update/Create can be supressed for all users by setting config parameter (tag|name).(allow_create|allow_update) to false.
